  "text": "The Sr22 resistance gene was identi ed in T. monococcum ssp. aegilopoides accession G-21 [CITATION_1] ) and in T. monococcum ssp. monococcum accession RL5244 [CITATION_2] . Sr22 was mapped on the long arm of chromosome 7A within a relatively large T. monococcum chromosome segment , which was recently shortened in new secondary recombinant hexaploid lines [CITATION_3] . Sr22 is e ective against all stem rust races listed in Table 1 , including QFCSC. Since both G3116 and DV92 are susceptible to QFCSC, the presence of Sr22 in these two lines can be ruled out.",
